cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the deployment and interference management of femtocellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes various frequency-allocation schemes to increase the spectral efficiency of the integrated network, which involves the use of information theory concepts. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the provision of high data-rate communications with improved quality of service, which is related to multimedia applications. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the self-organization of highly dense femtocellular deployments, which involves the use of control systems. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the interference management between femtocellular and macrocellular networks can have security implications, making this sub-category a possibility.
